sentences: Jeri Brown (born 1952 in Missouri) is an American jazz singer, songwriter, and professor.
In 1991, Brown signed with the Canadian Justin Time label.
In 1992 she recorded Unfolding The Peacocks with Kirk Lightsey and Peter Leitch.
In 1998, she worked on the album Zaius with David Murray, Don Braden, John Hicks, Curtis Lundy and Avery Sharpe.
Brown moved to Canada in 1989, and in the 1990s she taught jazz history, improvisation and vocal technique at Concordia University in Montreal, Quebec.
